#. <section class="sutta" id="an9.24"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an9.24:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 9"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 9"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an9.24:0.2"
msgid "3. Sattāvāsavagga"
msgstr "3. Abodes of Sentient Beings"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an9.24:0.3"
msgid "24. Sattāvāsasutta"
msgstr "24. Abodes of Sentient Beings"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an9.24:1.1"
msgid "“Navayime, bhikkhave, sattāvāsā."
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are nine abodes of sentient beings."

msgctxt "an9.24:1.2"
msgid "Katame nava?"
msgstr "What nine?"

msgctxt "an9.24:1.3"
msgid ""
"Santi, bhikkhave, sattā nānattakāyā nānattasaññino, seyyathāpi manussā, "
"ekacce ca devā, ekacce ca vinipātikā."
msgstr ""
"There are sentient beings that are diverse in body and diverse in "
"perception, such as human beings, some gods, and some beings in the "
"underworld."

msgctxt "an9.24:1.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ paṭhamo sattāvāso. (1)"
msgstr "This is the first abode of sentient beings."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an9.24:2.1"
msgid ""
"Santi, bhikkhave, sattā nānattakāyā ekattasaññino, seyyathāpi devā "
"brahmakāyikā paṭhamābhinibbattā."
msgstr ""
"There are sentient beings that are diverse in body and unified in "
"perception, such as the gods reborn in Brahmā’s Group through the first "
"absorption."

msgctxt "an9.24:2.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ dutiyo sattāvāso. (2)"
msgstr "This is the second abode of sentient beings."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an9.24:3.1"
msgid ""
"Santi, bhikkhave, sattā ekattakāyā nānattasaññino, seyyathāpi devā ābhassarā."
msgstr ""
"There are sentient beings that are unified in body and diverse in "
"perception, such as the gods of streaming radiance."

msgctxt "an9.24:3.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ tatiyo sattāvāso. (3)"
msgstr "This is the third abode of sentient beings."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an9.24:4.1"
msgid ""
"Santi, bhikkhave, sattā ekattakāyā ekattasaññino, seyyathāpi devā subhakiṇhā."
msgstr ""
"There are sentient beings that are unified in body and unified in "
"perception, such as the gods replete with glory."

msgctxt "an9.24:4.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ catuttho sattāvāso. (4)"
msgstr "This is the fourth abode of sentient beings."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an9.24:5.1"
msgid ""
"Santi, bhikkhave, sattā asaññino appaṭisaṃvedino, seyyathāpi devā "
"asaññasattā."
msgstr ""
"There are sentient beings that are non-percipient and do not experience "
"anything, such as the gods who are non-percipient beings."

msgctxt "an9.24:5.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ pañcamo sattāvāso. (5)"
msgstr "This is the fifth abode of sentient beings."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an9.24:6.1"
msgid ""
"Santi, bhikkhave, sattā sabbaso rūpasaññānaṃ samatikkamā paṭighasaññānaṃ "
"atthaṅgamā nānattasaññānaṃ amanasikārā ‘ananto ākāso’ti ākāsānañcāyatanūpagā."
msgstr ""
"There are sentient beings that have gone totally beyond perceptions of form. "
"With the ending of perceptions of impingement, not focusing on perceptions "
"of diversity, aware that ‘space is infinite’, they have been reborn in the "
"dimension of infinite space."

msgctxt "an9.24:6.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ chaṭṭho sattāvāso. (6)"
msgstr "This is the sixth abode of sentient beings."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an9.24:7.1"
msgid ""
"Santi, bhikkhave, sattā sabbaso ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘anantaṃ "
"viññāṇan’ti viññāṇañcāyatanūpagā."
msgstr ""
"There are sentient beings that have gone totally beyond the dimension of "
"infinite space. Aware that ‘consciousness is infinite’, they have been "
"reborn in the dimension of infinite consciousness."

msgctxt "an9.24:7.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ sattamo sattāvāso. (7)"
msgstr "This is the seventh abode of sentient beings."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an9.24:8.1"
msgid ""
"Santi, bhikkhave, sattā sabbaso viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘natthi kiñcī’"
"ti ākiñcaññāyatanūpagā."
msgstr ""
"There are sentient beings that have gone totally beyond the dimension of "
"infinite consciousness. Aware that ‘there is nothing at all’, they have been "
"reborn in the dimension of nothingness."

msgctxt "an9.24:8.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ aṭṭhamo sattāvāso. (8)"
msgstr "This is the eighth abode of sentient beings."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an9.24:9.1"
msgid ""
"Santi, bhikkhave, sattā sabbaso ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma "
"nevasaññānāsaññāyatanūpagā."
msgstr ""
"There are sentient beings that have gone totally beyond the dimension of "
"nothingness. They have been reborn in the dimension of neither perception "
"nor non-perception."

msgctxt "an9.24:9.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ navamo sattāvāso. (9)"
msgstr "This is the ninth abode of sentient beings."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an9.24:10.1"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, nava sattāvāsā”ti."
msgstr "These are the nine abodes of sentient beings.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an9.24:10.2"
msgid "Catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
